This paper deals with the problem of gathering mobile agents on a grid, which is a classic problem in distributed computing. The use of initial information, unbounded memory, and randomization are all important aspects of this problem, and are likely to be studied in the sub-categories of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Machine Learning (cs.LG), and Systems and Control (cs.SY).
